        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 9:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles southwest of Wild Horse Point to 9
miles west of Arlington to 9 miles east of Sugar City. Movement was
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blue Lake and Arlington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
